				<td colspan="2"><span>Well honestly . . 
<br />

<br />
Swarm kiting is a GREAT deal &quot;Easier&quot; to pull off than AE kiting (post AE range nerf)  . . at least in my opinion - Done properly there is virtually no risk to the Kiter - and still grants a relatively high EXP/time ratio.
<br />

<br />
So the  statement:
<br />

<br />
###########################
<br />
Learn to swarm kite. It won't kill you. 
<br />
###########################
<br />

<br />
Seems a bit seems a bit ill informed in regard the learning curves associated with the various skills of a bard - (Spelled out . . . . if you can AE kite - you can easily Swarm kite, but  being able to easily Swarm Kite does NOT mean you can necessarily AE Kite high end mobs).
<br />

<br />
As far as:
<br />
##########################################
<br />
We had too many half-assed bards who were only rolled up due to the insane PL exp ability of AE kiting. 
<br />
##########################################
<br />

<br />
I can't say I know what you mean - is your server populated with half assed bards?? my condolences - you have an opportunity to shine  . . I'm sure.
<br />

<br />

<br />
My gripe is that this nerf has removed a piece of the game, for me, that was still fun and challenging - 
<br />

<br />
If you've AE kited any number of high level mobs, you know that one slip up . . one Zone Lag . .  one zig when you should have zagged equals instant death or at least a HUGE dent in your HP bar - if you survive, the thrill of beating the challenge is heightened further.
<br />

<br />
Let's say <b><i>you</i> </b>have a particular mob  you personally enjoyed the challenge of besting . or particular zone or a particular style.
<br />

<br />
Then Sony makes some changes - they've now made it impossible to for you to do what you really enjoyed doing - that thing you got a kick out of,  really harmed no one - nor did it exploit the game - but only you and a minority of folks knew about it or liked it , so no one really seemed to mind when Sony Nerfed it - in fact many folks simply said &quot;Suck it up&quot; learn to do &quot;X&quot;, like the rest of &quot;XX_class_01&quot;.  
<br />

<br />
I can't imagine that those types of responses would make you feel any better about your perceived loss / injustice . . . heaven forbid you should get such non-support from within your own community of fellow &quot;XX_class_01&quot; buds.
<br />

<br />
I'm pretty sure that if Wizards or Druids were no longer able to cast Damage spells on Moving target - the Cry would be heard around the world!! They didn't do it to them today - and I don't suspect they'll do it - ever.
<br />

<br />
All in all  . .. you're right . . I could go back to Swarm kiting . . .  30+ or so Treant+Arachnids+Blood Ravens in PoN is a nice little swarm - they each drop in about 2+ ticks so you do have to be quick on your &quot;Boots of the Mosquito&quot; . . and Hobgoblins / Nettlings are still decent experience - 
<br />

<br />
but let me say . . 
<br />

<br />
It's <b><i>NOT </i> </b> the same challenge for me . . it's not as exciting . . it's not as fun . . that's why this change is less than ideal in my eyes.</span></td>
