				<td colspan="2"><span>I doubt they are taking aim at existing swarm kiting.  But it IS limited to level 57 mobs.  Swarms tend to be smaller in total mob count than the AE kites that were being a problem.  
<br />

<br />
Because of the chant-down time, its more efficient to swarm 7 or 8 and grab a single add 22 times after each kill than it is to start with 29 or 30.  If you have a huge hoard, you have to choose between breaking early and hence chanting longer or potentially losing the mob.
<br />

<br />
7-10 mobs running a bigger circle doesnt create as much lag as 30 mobs running a tight circle.  7-10 mobs still leaves pulling opportunities for folks around the bard.
<br />

<br />
Now swarming beyond what has been, they are aiming to prevent.  Higher XPS from higher level mobs would make swarming just too powerful in their minds (they may be right).  There is no reason we couldn't 1-on-1 charm kite with the new charm or even 1-on-2 to get the swarm-esque benefit, tho.  And I have seen ideas that might well work for tactics changes that might make swarming harder but possible.</span></td>
